author: @NPatel-vk5sk
text: those of you who got an empty csv file - make sure 1) in regex, you are also taking in the "negative" numbers - use r'.*?(\-?\d{1,8}\.\d{1,8}M?B?|N/A)%?' 2) At the place where you check for "billion" or "million" - you have convert the "value" string into a list and then use "if "B" in listvalue:". You can convert a string (value) into a list by using list(string).

author: @Juju-rx8cf
text: Great video, great channel! :) Yet I believe your regex does not take into account minus signs, comas and Ks... Companies can lose money sometimes... I am no regex expert but here is how I would have done it : r'.*?(\-?\d{1,8}?,?\d{1,8}\.\d{1,8}M?B?K?|N/A)%?'  Can you confirm? :)
